13. A fast food restaurant manager wants to reduce the spread of employee hourly wages by adding $1 to each employee's wage. Is this effective?
**No** — Adding a constant to every value increases the mean by that constant but does not change the spread. The standard deviation remains the same because deviations from the mean are unchanged.

